description:
&lt;p&gt;Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust has exciting opportunities for people who are interested in working in a Health environment while completing an Apprenticeship Standard, over 15 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is strictly subject to satisfactory completion of the Care Certificate Programme which must be completed in the first 12 weeks of commencement of post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as the minimum educational criteria for the post we are looking for enthusiastic people with a professional attitude, excellent communication skills, positive work ethic and good interpersonal skills. They will also need to demonstrate a willingness to work, motivation, have the ability to work as part of a team and be willing to learn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Apprentice Standard that you will undertake includes: a Care Certificate and completion of apprenticeship level 2 standard. Employees Rights and Responsibilities, and any other relevant in-house courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Apprentice Standard that you will undertake includes: a Care Certificate and completion of apprenticeship level 2 standard. And any other relevant in-house courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants, on completion of their apprenticeship programme, will be able to apply for vacancies within Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust, where their qualifications meet the requirements for the post, and will be guaranteed an interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 GCSE&#96;s level A - E (including Maths and English)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Dawn Waugh Job title: Health Apprentice Lead Facilitator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Dawn.Waugh@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01912031415&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 6th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
